commText: Gaikwad and Ravindra are at the crease. Gaikwad is on strike. Siraj will open the attack

Siraj to Gaikwad, FOUR, cracking shot, Ruturaj is off and running - friendly short ball from Siraj, shoulders arms up to the right-hander, Gaikwad swivels across and then hammers the pull over square leg for a boundary
Siraj to Gaikwad, no run, short of a good length and angling adcross the right-hander, stays a fraction low and goes under Gaikwad's poke, bounced through to the keeper
Siraj to Gaikwad, no run, back of a length and well wide of off, punched to the right of backward point where Mayank Dagar makes an acrobatic stop, saved a certain boundary
Siraj to Gaikwad, no run, on a good length and shaping away from outside off - Gaikwad covers the line, lifts his bat and lets it go

Siraj to Gaikwad, FOUR, uppish and four, fuller length delivery and shaping away from wide of off, Gaikwad is lured into the drive, he doesn't get on top of the bounce, but does manage to find the gap square past cover-point
Siraj to Gaikwad, no run, on a good length and holding its line outside off - stayed very low and burst under Gaikwad's bat, bouncing through to the keepert
Yash Dayal, left-arm fast medium, comes into the attack

Yash Dayal to Ravindra, FOUR, streaky and four, fuller length delivery and holding its line outside off - Ravindra goes hard on the drive, gets a big inside edge that runs away past the stumps and away from Rawat's reach
Yash Dayal to Ravindra, 1 run, on a good length and angling into the left-hander, worked in front of square on the on-side, to the left of mid-on for a single
Yash Dayal to Gaikwad, no run, back of a length and at the hips, tucked straight to the fielder at short fine
Yash Dayal to Gaikwad, no run, lovely delivery, short of a good length and a hint of shape away from off, Gaikwad has a poke at that and nearly edges it through to the keeper
Yash Dayal to Gaikwad, no run, much better from Yash - pitched up and pushed across with the natural angle, dragged Gaikwad into the drive and beats him on the outside edge
Yash Dayal to Gaikwad, no run, beaten, short of a good length and angling across the right-hander, brings out a loose waft and Gaikwad's beaten on the outside edge
Siraj to Ravindra, wide, Siraj loses his line and spills one well down the leg-side, called as a wide

Siraj to Ravindra, FOUR, beautifully played, fuller length delivery and angling into the pads, Ravindra lets the ball come, brings his wrists into play and then flicks it backward of square on the on-side, beat the despairing dive from the fielder in the deep

Siraj to Ravindra, 1 run, Ravindra gets lucky now - on a good length and angling back into the left-hander, Ravindra was early into the tuck, closed the bat-face and the leading edghe popped over Siraj's outstretched right-hand
Siraj to Gaikwad, 1 run, Mayank has saved a few more runs here - fuller length delivery and well wide of off, driven to the right of cover where he threw himself and made a one-handed save
Siraj to Ravindra, 1 run, fuller length delivery on the stumps, driven to the left of mid-on and they're off for a quick single
Siraj to Gaikwad, 1 run, short of a good length and well wide of off, chopped to the left of cover-point for a single

Siraj to Ravindra, SIX, top-edge and six, luck running Ravindra's way at the moment - banged in short and he's late on the pull, gets a massive top-edge, was always a safe shot with fine leg inside the ring, this one has enough power to sail over the ropes
Yash Dayal to Gaikwad, 1 run, fuller length delivery outside off, Gaikwad plays with an angled bat and runs it backward of square on the off-side for a single
Yash Dayal to Ravindra, FOUR, more runs, too full and too straight from Dayal - on the pads and it's whipped away backward of square on the on-side, beats the man in the ring and races away
Yash Dayal to Ravindra, no run, fuller length delivery outside off, Ravindra leans across and defends it with an open face to cover-point
Yash Dayal to Ravindra, 1 run, on a good length and just outside off, driven to the right of mid-off for a single
Yash Dayal to Gaikwad, FOUR, wrong line from Dayal, short and at the pads - Gaikwad gets inside the line and nudged it very fine, beats the man in the ring and runs away
Yash Dayal to Gaikwad, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Yash Dayal to Gaikwad, out Caught by Green!! Edged and caught! Green on the second attempt and he has big hands, this is some reward for Dayal - troubled Gaikwad with the angle and has finally nailed him - pitched up and pushed across with the angle, Gaikwad had to reach out on the drive, there's no control over the shot and gets a thick edge to slip's right. Green was quick to react, but the ball popped out, fortunately for RCB - he's alert enough to grab the rebound off the knee. Gaikwad c Green b Yash Dayal 15(15) [4s-3]
Gaikwad vs LA Fast in the PP (Overs 1-6) in the IPL Runs: 200 Balls: 178 Dismissals: 10 Avg: 20 SR: 112.35 4s/6s: 21/8 Dots: 88
Ajinkya Rahane, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Alzarri Joseph, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Alzarri Joseph to Ravindra, SIX, cracking shot, pacy short ball from Alzarri - but this is at the hips of Ravindra, he swivels across anmd then hammers the pull over long leg for a maximum
Alzarri Joseph to Ravindra, 1 run, Alzarri shortens the length around off, punched to the left of cover-point for a single
Alzarri Joseph to Rahane, no run, a long LBW appeal, but they ain't reviewing it, must've been an inside edge, too close to dab and Rahane squeezed an under-edge onto his front-pad
Alzarri Joseph to Rahane, 1 run, back of a length and just outside off, Rahane runs it down towards third man for a single
Alzarri Joseph to Ravindra, wide, short and down leg, Ravindra was looking to help it on its way with the pull and missed, called as a wide

Alzarri Joseph to Ravindra, 2 runs, just short of Faf at mid-off, and he then has to chase, does well to keep them down to a couple - back of a length and well wide of off, flat-batted uppishly towards mid-off and had faf diving forward on the catch
Alzarri Joseph to Ravindra, no run, short of a good length and around the off-stump channel, Ravindra swings and is struck high on the body

Match Highlights (1-5 overs) * Ruturaj scores a boundary first ball of the innings * Impact sub Dayal bowls a neat first over, beats the bat twice * Ravindra hits Siraj for a four and a six * Dayal strikes, Ruturaj edges one to first slip * Joseph greeted with a first ball six by Ravindra * CSK start solidly, are 49/1 after five overs
Yash Dayal to Rahane, no run, Dayal is bowling beautifrully to the right-handers, pitched up and the angle takes the ball away from Rahane's rteach, past the waft and into the gloves of the keeper
Yash Dayal to Rahane, no run, fuller length delivery and shaping across the right-hander - Rahane was looking to jam it out and missed

Yash Dayal to Rahane, SIX, Rahane throws his hands on a length ball and sends it carving over mid-off for a maximum - back of a length and angling across the right-hander, he's smote it on the rise and the timing is sublime, into the stands at long-off
Yash Dayal to Rahane, 2 runs, fuller length delivery and well wide of off - Rahane plays with a bent knee as he slices the drive over backward point, comes back for the second

Yash Dayal to Rahane, 2 runs, a mistimed drive, but the ball drops over Faf's right shoulder - fuller length delivery and just outside off, Rahane went hard on the drive, came off the thick edge and he's lucky to have cleared the infield

Yash Dayal to Rahane, 3 runs, more runs, this is so frustrating for RCB - yorker length delivery and it was jammed in front of cover-point, the run was always there, but the fielder has a shy at the bowler's end, no one's backing him up and Rahane gets a couple of more runs in the bargain
Karn Sharma, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Karn Sharma to Rahane, no run, flighted delivery on middle and leg, worked off the back-foot to the bowler
Karn Sharma to Rahane, 2 runs, loopy delivery on middle and leg, clipped in front of square on the on-side and they race back for the second
Karn Sharma to Rahane, no run, pushed through by Karn - Rahane backs away and finds backward point with the cut
Karn Sharma to Rahane, 1 run, Karn dragged the length back as Rahane came down the pitch, worked down to long-on for a single

Karn Sharma to Ravindra, SIX, a long hop and it's been hammered - dragged half-way by Karn, Ravindra rocks back and then thumps it powerfully over wide mid-wicket, there's a fielder in the deep, but he's well away from the ball
Karn Sharma to Ravindra, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Karn Sharma to Ravindra, out Caught by Rajat Patidar!! Karn has his man now - was pushed through quicker and at the stumps, Ravindra went down on his knee as he looked to play the slog-sweep - hit it hard and hit it flat, straight down Patidar's throat at deep backward square leg. The dangerous Ravindra departs and RCB can heave a sigh of relief. Ravindra c Rajat Patidar b Karn Sharma 37(15) [4s-3 6s-3]
They've taken the strategic break at the fall of Ravindra
Daryl Mitchell, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Mayank Dagar, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Mayank Dagar to Rahane, 1 run, full outside off, just a touch early through his drive but it goes into the gap and through to sweeper cover
Mayank Dagar to Mitchell, no run, length delivery outside off, punched straight to point
Mayank Dagar to Mitchell, no run, length delivery on off-stump, saw the batter running down the track and dropped it just a touch shorter, just holds in the surface a touch too
Mayank Dagar to Mitchell, no run, shade fuller and just outside off, Mitchell plays back again as he knocks it towards cover, bit of bite and turn again

Mayank Dagar to Mitchell, 1 run, flatter delivery outside off, Mitchell shuffles across his stumps early and knocks it towards cover for a quick single, even a quick pick-up and throw from Faf can't find Rahane short

Mayank Dagar to Rahane, no run, fired in quicker on a length, angles into the pads and skids through this time, beats Rahane who was looking to turn it into the leg-side and hits his pad, would've gone down leg
Karn Sharma to Mitchell, no run, tossed up full on off-stump, Mitchell prods forward and knocks it towards cover
Karn Sharma to Mitchell, SIX, Mitchell goes big! Floated up full on off-stump, this was in his zone and he cleared his front-leg and mowed it straight down the ground, cleared the ropes so easily
Karn Sharma to Mitchell, SIX, two in a row! Tossed up full outside off, more than enough room for Mitchell to free his arms this time and he launches it over long-off, Karn Sharma under pressure
Karn Sharma to Mitchell, 1 run, length delivery on middle, Mitchell covers his stumps and works it away towards mid-wicket for one, good cricket

Karn Sharma to Rahane, 1 run, tossed up full on middle, gently worked away towards wide mid-on, only went to the edge of the ring and Rahane was looking for two but the man running in from long-on was quick
Karn Sharma to Mitchell, 1 run, full on middle, pushed down the ground to long on, good over for CSK, 15 off it
Mayank Dagar to Mitchell, 1 run, full on off-stump, Mitchell leans right across his stumps and fetches it with a sweep, gets it to the left of short fine-leg but there's protection in the deep
Mayank Dagar to Rahane, 1 run, full and just outside off, Rahane makes room and skips down the track before slapping it down to long-off
Mayank Dagar to Mitchell, no run, full on off-stump, driven straight back to the bowler
Mayank Dagar to Mitchell, no run, flatter delivery on middle, knocked back towards the bowler who hops to his right to stop it
Mayank Dagar to Mitchell, 1 run, fired in full outside off, Mitchell was looking for a big one and could only jam it out towards cover
Mayank Dagar to Rahane, 1 run, flatter delivery on middle, worked away to wide long-on
Cameron Green, right-arm medium, comes into the attack

Match Highlights (6-10 overs) * Rahane flat bats Dayal for a six over long-off * Ravindra gets to a brisk 37 off 15 balls, before holing out * Karn Sharma gets the breakthrough for RCB * Dagar bowls a good first over, concedes just two runs * Mitchell hits Karn Sharma for two sixes down the ground * CSK in control of the chase at 92/2 after 10 overs
Green to Rahane, wide, good length delivery that just angles down leg, Rahane looked to glance it fine and missed, called a wide

Green to Rahane, SIX, into the stands! Just back of a length on middle-leg, poor line again and Rahane seemingly was waiting for the short one, he was sitting back and pulled this away to the deep backward square leg with ease
Green to Rahane, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Green to Rahane, out Caught by Maxwell!! Superb catch from Maxwell in the deep! Rahane perishes but he's done his job. Back of a length on middle-leg again, didn't rise as much though and Rahane was hanging back again, he just checked his pull this time and it went off the top half, was still traveling but Maxwell intercepted it on the deep backward square leg ropes. He was a few yards in but did brilliantly to run to his left and jump at the right second to reel it in. Much needed for RCB, just keeps the morale up. Rahane c Maxwell b Green 27(19) [6s-2]
Shivam Dube, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Green to Shivam Dube, 1 run, back of a length and slanting across just outside off, Shivam Dube shafts the pull towards mid-wicket off the toe end
Green to Mitchell, 1 run, good length delivery on middle, Mitchell shuffles across and tucks it away towards deep square leg
Green to Shivam Dube, no run, banged in short and at good pace, rushes Shivam Dube as he looks to take it on and beats him, Anuj Rawat fumbles behind the stumps
Green to Shivam Dube, 1 run, good length delivery slanting across outside off, Shivam Dube flashed at it and got a thick outside edge, went down to third man who was placed quite fine
FYI: Shivam Dube has come in as an impact sub for Mustafizur
Alzarri Joseph [1.0-0-11-0] is back into the attack
Alzarri Joseph to Shivam Dube, 1 run, length delivery outside off, cut away towards deep backward point
Alzarri Joseph to Mitchell, 1 run, good length delivery just outside off, Mitchell was hanging back looking to heave it away, rushed him and went towards mid-on off the splice
Alzarri Joseph to Shivam Dube, 1 run, back of a length on middle, takes it on with a pull but is clearly rushed again, mistimes it and it goes towards deep mid-wicket

Alzarri Joseph to Mitchell, 1 run, and again, the zippy pace of Alzarri Joseph rushes the batter, good length just outside off, Mitchell was waiting on the backfoot looking to heave it away again and mistimed it down to long-on
Just something brewing here
Alzarri Joseph to Shivam Dube, 1 run, back of a length on middle, mistimed pull goes towards square leg this time

Alzarri Joseph to Mitchell, 2 runs, pace off this time, back of a length and just outside off, Mitchell sat deep in his crease and waited for it before pulling it away towards deep mid-wicket, no timing again but it was in the gap, they shuffle back for two
RCB review. There was a loud appeal for caught behind and Anuj Rawat looked very confident

Green to Shivam Dube, no run, nothing on UltraEdge, review lost! Banged into the deck and going across the batter again, was just outside off, rushed him with the pace and cramped him for room as he looked to pull, just about went over the top-edge, was extremely close but nothing on UltraEdge to RCB's plight
Green to Shivam Dube, 1 run, in the air but safe! Again Green goes back of a length and into the body, cramps him for room as he looks to pull and lobs up, lands safely in the square leg region
Green to Mitchell, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Green to Mitchell, out Caught by Rajat Patidar!! The short-ball tactic finally pays off for RCB! Looks like RCB had a plan and they stuck with it. Banged into the deck on off-stump, Mitchell made a bit of room by backing away and looked to flat-bat this over long-on, didn't get nearly enough and it came off the top half. Went straight down Patidar's throat at long-on and another timely wicket for RCB. Mitchell c Rajat Patidar b Green 22(18) [6s-2]
Green starts round the wicket to Jadeja
Ravindra Jadeja, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Green to Jadeja, no run, good length delivery angling into the batter on off-stump, Jadeja has to get on his toes as he drops it into the off-side
Green to Jadeja, wide, excellent take from Anuj Rawat, very short on middle, sailed over Jadeja's head, Rawat timed his jump to perfection behind the stumps and kept it in
Green to Jadeja, 2 runs, full outside off, driven out through to deep extra cover, decently timed but not enough to beat the sweeper running to his left
Green to Jadeja, 1 run, back of a length on off-stump, pulled away towards deep mid-wicket
Two left-handers at the crease and Maxwell is brought into the attack
Glenn Maxwell, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Maxwell to Jadeja, no run, tossed up full on off-stump, slides on with the arm and catches a thick inside edge onto the pads as Jadeja looks to drive it into the off-side
Maxwell to Jadeja, SIX, in the slot and it goes the distance! Tossed up a little too full on off-stump, a real freebie and Jadeja smoked it over long-on with a clean swing of the blade
Maxwell to Jadeja, 1 run, full on middle, pushed down the ground to long on
Maxwell to Shivam Dube, no run, fired in flat on middle, knocked straight back to the bowler
Maxwell to Shivam Dube, no run, flatter delivery just outside off, Shivam Dube presses back and cuts, backward point does well to stop it after tumbling to his left

Maxwell to Shivam Dube, no run, flatter delivery and just pushed down leg, Shivam Dube looked to glance it fine and there was a loud appeal for caught behind, umpire stood unmoved so it might've brushed thigh pad
53 needed off 36. On paper, the equation might favor CSK but they've been put under a bit of pressure in the last few overs
Mohammed Siraj [2.0-0-23-0] is back into the attack

Siraj to Jadeja, 2 runs, full and on the pads, lovely looking whip into the leg-side towards deep mid-wicket, was very well timed and Maxwell had to be at the top of his game, stopped it with a slide to his right

Siraj to Jadeja, 2 runs, too straight again, Siraj gets away with another, back of a length and just down leg, Jadeja got inside the line and pulled it very fine, long leg got around to cut it off but two more taken
Siraj to Jadeja, 1 run, back of a length on middle, pulled down to deep square leg
Siraj to Shivam Dube, 1 run, back of a length on middle-off, doesn't rise and Shivam Dube crunches the pull towards deep square leg, can't beat Maxwell to his right though
Siraj to Jadeja, 1 run, back of a length on middle, pulled down to deep square leg
Siraj to Shivam Dube, no run, back of a length slower delivery, goes across and Shivam Dube is through his pull too early
Timeout. This game is beautifully poised. 46 needed from the last 5 overs is usually no real task for the batting team but RCB have bowled fairly well since the 10th over.

Match Highlights (11-15 overs) * Cam Green strikes off his second ball, good catch by Maxi in the deep * Rahane falls after scoring a promising 27 * Mitchell holes out to long-on, Green gets a second wicket * Jadeja slams Maxwell for a six over long-on * Game evenly poised, CSK need 46 off the final 5 overs
Green round the wicket to Jadeja again
Cameron Green [2.0-0-15-2] is back into the attack
Green to Jadeja, 1 run, good length delivery on off-stump, tucked down towards mid-on gently, they thought of two but it wasn't on

Green to Shivam Dube, FOUR, right into the gap! Back of a length and on the hips, this didn't rise much, Shivam Dube got inside the line and used the pace to pull it away right into the gap between deep backward square leg and long leg
Green to Shivam Dube, wide, banged in very short, that sailed over the batter and Shivam Dube is a fairly tall man

Green to Shivam Dube, 3 runs, very clever batting, back of a length and outside off, Shivam Dube hung back and just opened the face of the blade to steer it up and over backward point, man running across to his right did really well to stop it with a dive but just pushed it too far back in, they get a third
Green to Jadeja, 1 run, length delivery just outside off, Jadeja charges at it and makes some room before slapping it down to sweeper cover
The two short balls for the over are done, Faf was seen talking to the umpire about just that

Green to Shivam Dube, 1 run, good length delivery on off-stump, Shivam Dube hung back looking to tuck it into the leg-side and got a thick inside edge onto the pads, it dribbled just off the surface and they pinch a single
Green to Jadeja, 1 run, full and just outside off, carved out towards deep point
CSK are right on par with the asking rate. It's up to RCB to make the play here
Alzarri Joseph [2.0-0-18-0] is back into the attack

Alzarri Joseph to Jadeja, 2 runs, length delivery just outside off, cut away towards deep point. Oh dear, comedy of errors, the throw that came back in hit the stumps at the keeper's end and the keeper then had a shy at the stumps at the other end while the bowler had turned and was walking back to his mark

Alzarri Joseph to Jadeja, 2 runs, excellent running agian, back of a length on middle, rushes Jadeja on the pull and it dribbles towards mid-wicket, Joseph runs to it himself but they're so quick between the wickets to pinch that second
Alzarri Joseph to Jadeja, 1 run, length delivery outside off, swatted down to long-on
Alzarri Joseph to Shivam Dube, wide, RCB seem to be going a little overboard with the short stuff, Alzarri Joseph bangs it far too short, that was never even going to be close to Dube

Alzarri Joseph to Shivam Dube, FOUR, expertly guided! RCB have telegraphed their intentions here, back of a length on off-stump, Shivam Dube hung back and stayed leg-side, let it come to him and just opened the face of the blade to steer it well to the left of third man
Alzarri Joseph to Shivam Dube, wide, banged in short and going over the batter's head, that's both short deliveries allowed being wasted in wides

Alzarri Joseph to Shivam Dube, byes, FOUR, my my that went at pace! Back of a length on middle, this was bowled at full-throttle, Shivam Dube backed away a little looking to run it down but it whistled past his visor, kept rising on Anuj Rawat and he tipped it over with his fingertips as he leapt looking to stop it, RCB cannot afford these
Anuj Rawat seems to have injured himself as well, that hit the fingertips and those really hurt as a keeper. Bit of a delay here as the physio attends to Rawat. He seems fine and is back on his feet
Alzarri Joseph to Shivam Dube, 1 run, good cricket again, good length delivery on off-stump, gently bunted towards mid-off for a quick single, even Faf isn't quick enough to stop the single
Very productive over for CSK that, it puts the pressure right back on RCB. Down to a run-a-ball now, 18 needed off 18
Mohammed Siraj [3.0-0-30-0] is back into the attack

Siraj to Shivam Dube, no run, yorker goes horribly wrong but Siraj gets away with it, nearly a waist-high full-toss on middle, Shivam Dube was sitting back expecting a short one and he just bunted it towards cover

Siraj to Shivam Dube, FOUR, 50-run stand comes up! This is just poor bowling, back of a length and on the hips, no one back at fine-leg and these are easy pickings for Dube as he tucks it away to the fine-leg fence
Siraj to Shivam Dube, no run, slower short ball outside off, Shivam Dube looks to reach it and tap it down and misses
Siraj to Shivam Dube, no run, low full-toss on off-stump, Shivam Dube finds cover with the drive

Siraj to Shivam Dube, FOUR, lovely shot! RCB just adamant about bowling short here and they're paying for it, back of a length on middle, was pace off, Shivam Dube backed away to free his arms and slapped it back over the bowler, both mid-on and mid-off were up
Siraj to Shivam Dube, no run, back of a length and slanting across outside off, Shivam Dube looks to slash it away and misses
10 needed off 12. Should be CSK through and through barring a miracle
Alzarri Joseph to Jadeja, 1 run, back of a length on leg-stump, pulled away to deep square leg
Alzarri Joseph to Shivam Dube, wide, full and just down leg, Shivam Dube looks to glance it fine and misses, will be a wide
Alzarri Joseph to Shivam Dube, no run, banged in short on middle, Shivam Dube looks to take it on and misses, just went over the gloves, called one for the over

Alzarri Joseph to Shivam Dube, SIX, high and mighty! Banged in short on middle, there's only one thing coming at Shivam Dube and he knows what it is, he sits back comfortably and nails the hook high and over the long leg ropes
RCB review. They've got nothing going for themselves here, just a review in desperation

Alzarri Joseph to Shivam Dube, leg byes, FOUR, that'll do well enough for CSK! They get their 2024 campaign off to a winning start! Fired in full and at the boots, was just a touch down leg, Shivam Dube looked to flick it and missed, brushed his boot and went down fine to the fine-leg ropes

23:54 Local Time, 18:24 GMT, 23:54 IST: The defending champions, under a new captain but very much following the same ethos, are off to a winning start. They extend their superb home record against RCB and it's now 8-1 in CSK's favor. Probably not quite the nail-biting thriller that some would've hoped for but this grand tournament is off and flying. RCB did very well earlier to post 173 after being in strife at 78/5. It was a fighting total but they would've known that they would have to bowl well because the wicket got a bit better to bat on. CSK's openers got off to a flier and Rachin, in particular, had a debut to remember as he blasted a 15-ball 37. RCB pulled things back slightly in the middle overs and kept things interesting. There was a barrage of short balls and it got them a couple of wickets but they failed to adapt once it stopped working for them. They kept banging it in short while the batters knew exactly what was coming at them. Although Dube was initially uncomfortable, he hung in there and along with Jadeja, got the job done.

CSK give their fans a win upon returning to their fortress. The packed house might not have had a chance to see their Thala out with the bat but they would've gotten what they bargained for. These are two fan-bases that love having a go at each other and the yellow-army take all the spoils tonight.

Faf du Plessis | RCB Captain: Always when you play, you get a bit of dip after the six overs. Chennai are a very good team in the middle overs, they squeeze you with their spinners. Maybe we were about 15-20 runs short, the pitch wasn’t as bad as we played in the first 10 overs. They were always ahead in the chase, we tried to squeeze and get a couple of wickets, but in the end we didn’t have enough runs. On this pitch, it is always better to bat first. Last year, the record was very skewed towards teams that batted first. The ball started to grip a bit with our spinners. Really good for Dinesh to set up his season, especially for someone who hasn’t played a lot of cricket. Anuj has shown some great promise for us, he showed great composure for a young guy and great power through the backend.

Rachin Ravindra: I think it was a pretty complete performance, we held our composure together towards the end, great hands from Jinx and Rutu as well. I wouldn't call myself a starter, I worked for around 3-4 days to get into the transition from red to white-ball. It was good, the training wicket was different, I wasn't sure if I was hitting well. Got a bit lucky at the start, but that helped me settle and get over my nervous energy. It's easier to settle into an environment when you know you have a couple of boys with whom you have hung around for a while.

Shivam Dube vs RCB in the IPL 46(32), Mumbai WS, 2021 95*(46), Mumbai DYP, 2022 52(27), Bengaluru, 2023 34*(28), Chennai, 2024 Total: 227 off 133, Avg: 113.50.50, SR: 170.67 4s/6s: 16/16 RCB in IPL season openers 2008: Lost to KKR by 140 runs 2017: Lost to SRH by 35 runs 2019: Lost to CSK by 7 wickets 2021: Won vs MI by 2 wickets 2024: Lost to CSK by 6 wickets CSK vs RCB at Chepauk Won by CSK: 8 Won by RCB: 1 (2008) Most wins against a team in the IPL 23 - MI vs KKR 21 - CSK vs RCB 21 - KKR vs PBKS 20 - MI vs CSK 19 - CSK vs DC Highest aggregate in an IPL game with no individual 50-plus score 349 - CSK vs RCB, Chennai, 2024 343 - GL vs RPS, Rajkot, 2017 343 - KKR vs CSK, Abu Dhabi, 2021 342 - PBKS vs RR, Mohali, 2014 337 - SRH vs KKR, Hyderabad, 2023

Ruturaj Gaikwad | CSK Captain: Total control I would say, right from the start (apart) from 2-3 overs. Would’ve loved 10-15 runs less but I think they played really well towards the end. I feel that was a big turning point to get Maxwell and Faf out. We got three quick wickets and it helped us control the next overs, that was the real turning point. I’ve always enjoyed it (captaincy), never felt it as an additional pressure. I had experience on how to handle it, never felt any pressure, obviously had Mahi (MS Dhoni) bhai as well. I think everyone in our squad are natural strokeplayers, I think even Jinks (Ajinkya Rahane) is playing really positively. Everyone knows their roles and which bowlers to take on. Role clarity really helps. Two-three things to work on, everyone batted well but I think if someone from the top 3 batted till the 15th over it would’ve been even easier.
Mustafizur Rahman | Player of the Match
